'''Steve Mounié''' (born 29 September 1994) is a Beninese professional [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/steve-mounie/249283/|title=Benin – S. Mounié – Soccerway – Results, fixtures, tables and statistics |publisher=Soccerway |accessdate=2013-08-15}}</ref> He has been [[Cap (sport)|capped]] by [[Benin national football team|Benin]] at senior international level, making his debut on 13 October 2015.
==Club career== ===Montpellier=== Mounié is a [[Montpellier HSC]] youth academy graduate. He made his first team debut on 28 October 2014 in a [[2014–15 Coupe de la Ligue]] round of 32 home match against [[AC Ajaccio]], replacing [[Jean Deza]] after 86 minutes; Montpellier lost the match 1–0.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/10/28/france/coupe-de-la-ligue/montpellier-herault-sport-club/athletic-club-ajaccien/1949315/|title=Montpellier vs Ajaccio 0–1 |publisher=Soccerway|date=29 October 2014}}</ref>
On 31 August 2015, Mounié was loaned to [[Nîmes Olympique]] of [[Ligue 2]] for the rest of the 2015–16 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Deux-recrues-pour-nimes/586626|title=Trois recrues pour Nîmes|work=L'Équipe|date=31 August 2015}}</ref> He was the club's top scorer for the season, with 11 goals in 33 competitive matches, all of them scored during the [[2015–16 Ligue 2|league campaign]].
On 29 June 2016, Mounié extended his contract with Montpellier by two years to 30 June 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Montpellier-steve-mounie-prolonge-son-contrat/700705|title=Montpellier : Steve Mounié prolonge son contrat|work=L'Équipe|date=29 June 2016}}</ref>
On 11 March 2017, Mounié scored for the fifth consecutive Ligue 1 match in a 3–2 home loss to [[FC Nantes|Nantes]]; it was his 13th league goal of the [[2016-17 Ligue 1|season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/sala-nets-winner-as-nantes-beat-montpellier.htm|title=Sala nets winner as Nantes beat Montpellier|publisher=ligue1.com|date=11 March 2017}}</ref>
===Huddersfield Town=== On 5 July 2017, Mounié joined newly-promoted [[Premier League]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] on a four-year deal for a club record fee of €13 million (£11.5 million) plus add-ons. The record fee surpassed the previous record £8 million (initial fee) that the club spent on [[Aaron Mooy]] from [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] a week earlier.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40503864|title=Steve Mounie: Huddersfield sign Montpellier striker for a club-record fee|publisher=BBC|date=5 July 2017}}</ref>
Mounié made his competitive debut on 12 August 2017, scoring twice in Huddersfield's first match in the division, a 3–0 win at [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Doyale|first1=Paul|title=Steve Mounié double gives Huddersfield perfect start against Crystal Palace|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/aug/12/crystal-palace-huddersfield-town-premier-league-match-report|work=The Guardian}}</ref> On 11 February 2018, he scored, assisted Mooy and forced an own goal in a 4–1 home win over [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42934991|title=Huddersfield Town 4–1 Bournemouth|date=2018-02-11|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-02-12|language=en-GB}}</ref>
